- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper deals with the computational bottleneck of the eigendecomposition of the graph Laplacian matrix, which is a common problem in graph algorithms. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Spectral embedding is a technique commonly used in network analysis, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a numerical algorithm based on Cholesky factorization, which is a common technique in numerical analysis. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a machine learning algorithm for graph clustering, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
